Coxal pores: small, circular, more concentrated on the outer part of pore-field, forming 3-4 irregular rows; only 2-3 pores from the internal row on each coxa larger; 
around
25-30 on legs 12-14 and about 17 pores on leg 15; pores of inner rows often separated by more than twice their own diameter, those of outermost row usually separated by less than their own diameter (Fig. 2b).
